HEADWORD: Apoda
<hw>Ap"o*da</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, <?/. See <er>Apod</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A group of cirripeds, destitute of footlike
organs.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An order of Amphibia without feet. See
<er>Ophiomorpha</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A group of worms without
appendages, as the leech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apodan</ent>⟦br⟧
